						<summary>

						<p>On two faces of a pillar lying near a well west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is engraved in archaic characters and it reads from the bottom to the top.</p>						

						<p>It mentions that Satyāditya of the Kāśyapa-gōtra, son of <hi rend="bold">Śaktikomāra Vikramāditya</hi> the great lord, and the grandson of the glorious <hi rend="bold">Chōḷa-Mahārājādhirāja Vikramāditya</hi> while ruling the <hi rend="bold">Siddhi</hi> one <hi rend="bold">thousand</hi> and the <hi rend="bold">Rēnāṇḍu seven thousand</hi> gave to Rēvaśarmma of the Kāśyapa-gōtra and a resident of Komaṟipāra, five <hi rend="italic">maruntru</hi> of land at Chiṟumbūru</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi>, Vol. XI. page 345. </p>						

						</summary>
